1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,900
Chen Haowei,

2
00:00:00,900 --> 00:00:02,330
can you teach me math?

3
00:00:01,290 --> 00:00:06,360
[Episode 3]
[A Confession from the Shooting Stars]

4
00:00:02,330 --> 00:00:03,130
Sure.

5
00:00:04,630 --> 00:00:06,700
Why did you draw sea turtles on the paper?

6
00:00:06,700 --> 00:00:08,940
Drawing sea turtles makes me so happy.

7
00:00:09,500 --> 00:00:11,350
Do sea turtles have this kind of use?

8
00:00:11,350 --> 00:00:12,440
Then teach me how to draw.

9
00:00:12,440 --> 00:00:13,170
Alright.

10
00:00:13,170 --> 00:00:14,970
Let me teach you the easiest way.

11
00:00:15,540 --> 00:00:18,110
First, draw a big oval,

12
00:00:19,150 --> 00:00:20,880
add a spiral in the middle,

13
00:00:23,260 --> 00:00:25,130
then 4 boomerangs.

14
00:00:25,150 --> 00:00:26,120
Boomerangs?

15
00:00:26,150 --> 00:00:27,050
Yes.

16
00:00:28,620 --> 00:00:31,690
And the most important big head.

17
00:00:32,920 --> 00:00:34,090
And a little tail.

18
00:00:34,520 --> 00:00:35,240
Easy, right?

19
00:00:35,240 --> 00:00:36,940
Big head and little tail.

20
00:00:38,530 --> 00:00:39,390
This is so cute.

21
00:00:39,390 --> 00:00:40,020
Thank you.

22
00:00:40,050 --> 00:00:41,090
Now I know.

23
00:00:42,600 --> 00:00:44,230
I've always wanted to ask you a question.

24
00:00:44,230 --> 00:00:45,060
What is it?

25
00:00:45,080 --> 00:00:46,410
Why do you keep smiling?

26
00:00:47,800 --> 00:00:48,600
-Do I?
-Look.

27
00:00:48,910 --> 00:00:50,380
You're smiling right now.

28
00:00:51,510 --> 00:00:53,070
Isn't that good?

29
00:00:53,250 --> 00:00:54,890
Not that. Don't you

30
00:00:54,920 --> 00:00:56,220
ever feel unhappy

31
00:00:56,240 --> 00:00:57,640
or sad?

32
00:01:01,620 --> 00:01:02,530
I...

33
00:01:02,980 --> 00:01:04,250
I don't know.

34
00:01:05,390 --> 00:01:07,130
Well, how about

35
00:01:07,130 --> 00:01:08,500
I teach you a new way?

36
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:09,500
Tell me then.

37
00:01:10,470 --> 00:01:11,840
Say it in your heart:

38
00:01:11,870 --> 00:01:13,640
"1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7."

39
00:01:14,440 --> 00:01:16,300
1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.

40
00:01:16,870 --> 00:01:17,970
Don't you

41
00:01:18,710 --> 00:01:19,910
feel calm?

42
00:01:20,310 --> 00:01:21,410
Why these numbers?

43
00:01:21,940 --> 00:01:23,280
Because they are

44
00:01:23,560 --> 00:01:25,770
the most mysterious numbers in the world.

45
00:01:25,770 --> 00:01:28,740
Some say they're numbers chosen by God,

46
00:01:28,770 --> 00:01:31,750
while others say
they're the password in the universe.

47
00:01:31,750 --> 00:01:33,000
But actually, they're just

48
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:34,770
cyclic numbers in math.

49
00:01:35,950 --> 00:01:37,550
When you multiply it by 1 to 6,

50
00:01:38,060 --> 00:01:39,860
the set of digits stays the same,

51
00:01:40,110 --> 00:01:41,759
the sequence doesn't change,

52
00:01:41,759 --> 00:01:42,800
and it's still

53
00:01:43,229 --> 00:01:44,539
those same 6 numbers.

54
00:02:26,390 --> 00:02:29,329
[Wishing Upon the Shooting Stars]

55
00:02:53,430 --> 00:02:54,370
Aren't you a top student?

56
00:02:54,370 --> 00:02:55,600
Chen Haowei, answer the phone, okay?

57
00:02:55,600 --> 00:02:56,470
Please.

58
00:02:56,470 --> 00:02:58,070
-Making such a silly mistake?
-I just want an explanation

59
00:02:58,070 --> 00:02:59,670
about what is wrong with my money.

60
00:02:59,670 --> 00:03:01,440
Just use Mr. Lin's money.

61
00:03:01,440 --> 00:03:02,080
After all, we tried our best...

62
00:03:02,080 --> 00:03:03,580
Yes, I know investment is risky.

63
00:03:03,580 --> 00:03:05,040
But you were so sure,

64
00:03:05,070 --> 00:03:06,170
and what happened?

65
00:03:06,210 --> 00:03:08,050
-Do you want our efforts to go to waste?
-You said bonds were good, so I got them.

66
00:03:08,050 --> 00:03:08,920
You said funds were good, so I got them.

67
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:10,450
1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.

68
00:03:11,410 --> 00:03:13,340
-1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.
-The bank is scared to see me.

69
00:03:13,340 --> 00:03:14,290
The bank won't lend me money.

70
00:03:14,290 --> 00:03:15,620
-1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.
-I can't finance anymore.

71
00:03:15,620 --> 00:03:16,760
What should I do?

72
00:03:16,760 --> 00:03:17,760
Why don't you go tell him?

73
00:03:17,760 --> 00:03:19,590
-1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.
-Help me, please,

74
00:03:19,590 --> 00:03:20,850
Chen Haowei.

75
00:03:21,850 --> 00:03:24,220
1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.

76
00:03:26,970 --> 00:03:28,970
1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.

77
00:03:41,170 --> 00:03:41,840
Excuse me,

78
00:03:41,870 --> 00:03:43,270
are you going to check in?

79
00:03:47,420 --> 00:03:48,120
Miss.

80
00:04:06,150 --> 00:04:07,150
Pick one.

81
00:04:21,350 --> 00:04:22,880
You really need direction.

82
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:24,090
Is He Xiangyong here?

83
00:04:24,090 --> 00:04:25,220
I'm looking for him.

84
00:04:27,190 --> 00:04:28,390
Bring the luggage in.

85
00:04:48,620 --> 00:04:50,620
So you're the comics artist

86
00:04:50,640 --> 00:04:52,370
that Xiangyong is in charge of?

87
00:04:55,430 --> 00:04:56,690
May I ask,

88
00:04:56,820 --> 00:04:57,790
how's our He Xiangyong

89
00:04:57,790 --> 00:04:59,190
at work

90
00:04:59,190 --> 00:04:59,850
in the company—

91
00:04:59,850 --> 00:05:00,580
Xixi!

92
00:05:00,610 --> 00:05:01,180
You...

93
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:01,800
You yelled so loudly.

94
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:03,060
You scared me to death.

95
00:05:04,470 --> 00:05:05,370
How's our He Xiangyong

96
00:05:05,370 --> 00:05:06,930
at work?

97
00:05:06,930 --> 00:05:08,550
His attitude

98
00:05:08,570 --> 00:05:10,800
and performance?

99
00:05:11,180 --> 00:05:11,980
Why...

100
00:05:12,080 --> 00:05:13,220
Why are you here?

101
00:05:16,260 --> 00:05:17,790
Weird. You know her too?

102
00:05:21,170 --> 00:05:23,140
Mr. He, you don't read comics.

103
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:24,520
She's really famous.

104
00:05:24,520 --> 00:05:26,110
Like "The Hunter's Gentle Vacation,"

105
00:05:26,110 --> 00:05:27,360
"Desserts, Seeds, and the Prophecy Diary,"

106
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:27,920
and "Goddess of Zandir,"

107
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:29,020
she drew all of them.

108
00:05:29,020 --> 00:05:30,550
I love reading her comics.

109
00:05:30,710 --> 00:05:32,280
Y-You're my idol.

110
00:05:35,420 --> 00:05:36,550
But why are you here?

111
00:05:38,300 --> 00:05:39,170
Do you have a room available?

112
00:05:39,170 --> 00:05:40,290
-What do you want to do?
-Yes.

113
00:05:40,290 --> 00:05:41,740
Our guest came here to stay, of course.

114
00:05:41,740 --> 00:05:43,400
What kind of question is that?

115
00:05:44,140 --> 00:05:45,110
No, Mr. He,

116
00:05:45,110 --> 00:05:46,170
the vacant room

117
00:05:46,170 --> 00:05:47,480
hasn't been tidied up
after the guest left.

118
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:48,040
Besides,

119
00:05:48,040 --> 00:05:50,210
I haven't cleaned the toilet yet.

120
00:05:50,210 --> 00:05:51,909
The vacant room also leaks.

121
00:05:51,909 --> 00:05:53,450
I don't think it's...

122
00:05:53,450 --> 00:05:54,250
suitable.

123
00:05:54,250 --> 00:05:55,659
How many days are you staying?

124
00:05:55,659 --> 00:05:56,320
Three days.

125
00:05:57,250 --> 00:05:58,020
Well, listen,

126
00:05:58,020 --> 00:05:59,650
our vacant room really leaks.

127
00:05:59,650 --> 00:06:00,660
The floor is all wet.

128
00:06:00,660 --> 00:06:01,390
Haowei.

129
00:06:01,990 --> 00:06:03,660
Take her to check in.

130
00:06:03,660 --> 00:06:03,890
Okay.

131
00:06:03,890 --> 00:06:04,750
Gosh, Xiaoyou!

132
00:06:07,520 --> 00:06:09,880
Take the guest's luggage to Room 201.

133
00:06:11,290 --> 00:06:13,360
Room 201 won't leak.

134
00:06:15,230 --> 00:06:16,460
Check in here.

135
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:20,360
Miss, this way please.

136
00:06:20,360 --> 00:06:21,220
Sorry for that.

137
00:06:22,220 --> 00:06:23,250
Dudu, come here.

138
00:06:23,270 --> 00:06:24,330
Stay out of the sun.

139
00:06:49,440 --> 00:06:51,100
What are you doing here alone?

140
00:06:53,210 --> 00:06:54,040
I'm reading

141
00:06:54,550 --> 00:06:55,810
and enjoying the view.

142
00:06:59,250 --> 00:07:00,450
Is it because of Xixi?

143
00:07:02,620 --> 00:07:03,420
What?

144
00:07:06,790 --> 00:07:08,020
Why do you know Xixi?

145
00:07:11,190 --> 00:07:12,660
I've read all her comics,

146
00:07:12,660 --> 00:07:14,210
and my friend is her managing editor.

147
00:07:14,210 --> 00:07:16,540
I don't need to report these
to you, right?

148
00:07:19,540 --> 00:07:21,610
But when Mr. He asked her something,

149
00:07:22,470 --> 00:07:24,000
why did you look so nervous?

150
00:07:27,140 --> 00:07:27,780
Did I?

151
00:07:29,880 --> 00:07:31,680
Are you afraid of a caterpillar?

152
00:07:31,880 --> 00:07:33,110
What caterpillar?

153
00:07:33,990 --> 00:07:34,990
I wasn't.

154
00:07:35,550 --> 00:07:36,550
I wasn't nervous.

155
00:07:39,780 --> 00:07:40,590
Are you hiding something

156
00:07:40,590 --> 00:07:41,780
about He Xiangyong?

157
00:07:43,909 --> 00:07:45,440
You're so imaginative.

158
00:07:55,650 --> 00:07:56,520
What?

159
00:08:00,620 --> 00:08:02,620
Have you dated He Xiangyong before?

160
00:08:06,950 --> 00:08:07,650
Answer me.

161
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:12,080
Yes.

162
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:14,290
And we were inseparable.

163
00:08:14,310 --> 00:08:16,840
We couldn't even be apart
even if we wanted to.

164
00:08:19,860 --> 00:08:21,030
Inseparable?

165
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:26,740
I'm relieved now.

166
00:08:27,820 --> 00:08:28,790
About what?

167
00:08:30,910 --> 00:08:31,740
Since you said so,

168
00:08:31,740 --> 00:08:33,799
it means you've never been together.

169
00:08:35,510 --> 00:08:36,610
Boring.

170
00:08:38,909 --> 00:08:39,909
Wait.

171
00:08:40,210 --> 00:08:41,250
You said we should keep a distance

172
00:08:41,250 --> 00:08:42,490
and stay away from each other.

173
00:08:42,490 --> 00:08:43,549
Why are you suddenly so concerned?

174
00:08:43,549 --> 00:08:44,550
What are you up to?

175
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:47,420
Nothing.

176
00:08:48,520 --> 00:08:50,520
Just looking out for you as a friend.

177
00:08:51,660 --> 00:08:52,860
Really?

178
00:08:54,130 --> 00:08:55,660
The way you just asked

179
00:08:55,660 --> 00:08:58,260
doesn't feel like concern
from a friend at all.

180
00:08:59,150 --> 00:09:01,020
Instead, it feels more like…

181
00:09:03,230 --> 00:09:03,990
Like what?

182
00:09:06,870 --> 00:09:09,410
Like you were projecting.

183
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:11,250
What's going on?

184
00:09:14,040 --> 00:09:14,570
Nothing.

185
00:09:15,030 --> 00:09:15,960
We're fine.

186
00:09:16,710 --> 00:09:19,080
She's asking if we're free.

187
00:09:21,500 --> 00:09:23,100
Where do you want to go later?

188
00:09:23,670 --> 00:09:24,540
Breathe.

189
00:09:26,550 --> 00:09:27,380
Breathe?

190
00:09:28,910 --> 00:09:31,950
She probably means
she wants to take a walk.

191
00:09:32,260 --> 00:09:33,130
Am I right?

192
00:09:35,330 --> 00:09:36,130
That's great.

193
00:09:36,670 --> 00:09:37,720
I can give you a ride.

194
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:38,820
You rent one yourself.

195
00:09:38,820 --> 00:09:41,480
I'm sure you want to ride one by yourself,
right?

196
00:09:50,300 --> 00:09:51,630
What are you looking at?

197
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:55,490
Why do you know Xixi so well?

198
00:09:56,360 --> 00:09:58,400
Maybe I'm just sincere.

199
00:10:02,730 --> 00:10:03,930
Sincere?

200
00:11:07,900 --> 00:11:08,870
I used to

201
00:11:08,890 --> 00:11:10,150
watch the sea the most.

202
00:11:11,050 --> 00:11:12,450
But I can only watch,

203
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:14,250
because I can't swim.

204
00:11:15,610 --> 00:11:17,520
Whenever I listen to the sound of the sea,

205
00:11:17,520 --> 00:11:19,950
I feel like I'm floating on the sea.

206
00:11:31,600 --> 00:11:32,600
What do you think?

207
00:11:35,850 --> 00:11:37,310
Let me take a photo for you.

208
00:11:44,190 --> 00:11:46,450
One, two, three.

209
00:11:57,720 --> 00:11:59,080
This is where you

210
00:11:59,640 --> 00:12:01,360
can come whenever you're fed up,

211
00:12:01,360 --> 00:12:02,660
need to let go,

212
00:12:02,680 --> 00:12:04,590
or just feel like relaxing.

213
00:12:06,280 --> 00:12:07,870
Just close your eyes by the sea

214
00:12:07,870 --> 00:12:09,240
and count:

215
00:12:09,950 --> 00:12:12,050
1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.

216
00:12:25,660 --> 00:12:26,460
Seven...

217
00:12:26,480 --> 00:12:28,290
Seven sevens are 49.

218
00:12:28,320 --> 00:12:29,240
Eight eights are 64.

219
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:30,240
Nine nines are 81.

220
00:12:31,450 --> 00:12:33,890
Or singing is alright.

221
00:12:34,010 --> 00:12:35,540
After that,

222
00:12:36,520 --> 00:12:38,540
you'll feel that everything
is not important

223
00:12:38,540 --> 00:12:40,340
and that your worries will disappear.

224
00:12:40,340 --> 00:12:41,050
Really.

225
00:12:41,420 --> 00:12:42,950
It really works like magic.

226
00:12:51,870 --> 00:12:53,730
Let me take another photo for you.

227
00:13:05,770 --> 00:13:06,500
Here we are.

228
00:13:11,190 --> 00:13:12,030
Li Wanzhe.

229
00:13:13,210 --> 00:13:14,640
Three bowls of shaved ice.

230
00:13:14,640 --> 00:13:15,630
Mung bean milk ice

231
00:13:15,630 --> 00:13:16,920
and jelly ice.

232
00:13:16,940 --> 00:13:17,410
This way.

233
00:13:17,410 --> 00:13:18,910
For Xixi...

234
00:13:18,960 --> 00:13:20,820
give her tri-color taro ball ice.

235
00:13:21,050 --> 00:13:22,030
The tri-color taro balls
have to be cooked fresh,

236
00:13:22,030 --> 00:13:23,000
so hurry up.

237
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:29,860
Hey, Angela.

238
00:13:29,890 --> 00:13:30,730
Haowei.

239
00:13:30,750 --> 00:13:31,750
Have you ordered?

240
00:13:31,950 --> 00:13:32,450
Yes.

241
00:13:32,470 --> 00:13:33,190
OK.

242
00:13:33,220 --> 00:13:34,060
Xiaoyou.

243
00:13:34,090 --> 00:13:35,050
You have a guest.

244
00:13:39,270 --> 00:13:40,470
Xixi, let me tell you.

245
00:13:40,590 --> 00:13:42,410
Wanzhe's shaved ice is super delicious.

246
00:13:42,410 --> 00:13:43,740
No bad picks at all.

247
00:13:43,910 --> 00:13:45,410
It's just that the tri-color taro balls

248
00:13:45,410 --> 00:13:46,120
might take a little while,

249
00:13:46,120 --> 00:13:48,050
because they're all freshly made.

250
00:13:51,100 --> 00:13:52,480
So thirsty. It's hot today.

251
00:13:52,480 --> 00:13:53,650
It's too hot.

252
00:13:58,790 --> 00:14:00,250
Here comes the shaved ice.

253
00:14:00,610 --> 00:14:01,710
Why is it so fast?

254
00:14:03,990 --> 00:14:04,820
Li Wanzhe,

255
00:14:04,840 --> 00:14:05,780
what is this?

256
00:14:06,510 --> 00:14:07,230
Shaved ice.

257
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:10,330
Li Wanzhe!

258
00:14:11,050 --> 00:14:12,650
He must have had heatstroke.

259
00:14:12,730 --> 00:14:13,260
Wanzhe.

260
00:14:13,280 --> 00:14:13,850
What is this?

261
00:14:13,850 --> 00:14:14,480
I'll give you a gua sha massage.

262
00:14:14,480 --> 00:14:16,220
Oh my god! I'm sorry.

263
00:14:16,220 --> 00:14:16,750
Sorry.

264
00:14:16,750 --> 00:14:17,220
Nothing, nothing.

265
00:14:17,220 --> 00:14:18,490
I'll do it again.

266
00:14:18,490 --> 00:14:19,720
Haowei, help me greet her.

267
00:14:19,720 --> 00:14:22,120
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

268
00:14:22,810 --> 00:14:23,990
Li Wanzhe!

269
00:14:31,950 --> 00:14:33,100
One day,

270
00:14:33,850 --> 00:14:35,100
the shell came home

271
00:14:35,480 --> 00:14:36,350
and said—

272
00:14:36,370 --> 00:14:38,500
I'm back (which sounds like "shell").

273
00:14:43,420 --> 00:14:45,350
Why don't vampires eat spicy food?

274
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:51,890
Because they only drink blood
(which sounds like "not spicy").

275
00:14:53,230 --> 00:14:53,780
Do you know—

276
00:14:53,780 --> 00:14:54,980
Just get to the point.

277
00:15:01,150 --> 00:15:02,750
What does that card mean?

278
00:15:02,770 --> 00:15:05,040
What does "direction" mean?

279
00:15:08,980 --> 00:15:10,560
Sometimes, cards

280
00:15:11,380 --> 00:15:12,800
are just a reminder,

281
00:15:13,670 --> 00:15:14,840
not an answer.

282
00:15:19,120 --> 00:15:19,860
Here.

283
00:15:22,340 --> 00:15:23,280
Thank you.

284
00:15:23,340 --> 00:15:24,470
Not now.

285
00:15:26,610 --> 00:15:27,380
Okay.

286
00:15:27,410 --> 00:15:28,450
Put it away.

287
00:15:31,190 --> 00:15:33,360
Yes, I wanted to put it away.

288
00:16:02,610 --> 00:16:03,710
What?

289
00:16:04,410 --> 00:16:05,610
Gua sha massage.

290
00:16:09,890 --> 00:16:11,230
It hurts!

291
00:16:11,260 --> 00:16:12,520
You feel pain now, huh?

292
00:16:12,900 --> 00:16:14,210
Of course.

293
00:16:14,740 --> 00:16:16,540
What play are you putting on now?

294
00:16:19,980 --> 00:16:21,110
Because of Xiaohai?

295
00:16:21,460 --> 00:16:23,220
Don't mention that name again.

296
00:16:23,600 --> 00:16:24,350
I really don't know

297
00:16:24,350 --> 00:16:25,600
why he keeps
confessing his feelings to me.

298
00:16:25,600 --> 00:16:27,510
Didn't you say you wanted to date someone?

299
00:16:27,510 --> 00:16:28,850
That kind of passionate love?

300
00:16:28,850 --> 00:16:29,820
Now that love has come your way,

301
00:16:29,820 --> 00:16:30,840
why are you overreacting?

302
00:16:30,840 --> 00:16:32,440
Just accept his confession.

303
00:16:33,250 --> 00:16:33,920
But

304
00:16:33,920 --> 00:16:36,240
I didn't know my wish
would really come true.

305
00:16:36,240 --> 00:16:37,680
You told me to accept it.

306
00:16:39,420 --> 00:16:39,980
Fine.

307
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:41,730
Even if my wish has to come true,

308
00:16:41,740 --> 00:16:43,200
Xiaohai can't be the one.

309
00:16:43,220 --> 00:16:45,430
Xiaohai is my best buddy.

310
00:16:45,470 --> 00:16:46,450
We play video games together,

311
00:16:46,450 --> 00:16:48,040
and now we're gonna date each other?

312
00:16:48,040 --> 00:16:49,140
Don't you think that is so weird?

313
00:16:49,140 --> 00:16:49,530
This...

314
00:16:49,530 --> 00:16:50,860
is impossible.

315
00:16:53,940 --> 00:16:55,710
So,

316
00:16:56,310 --> 00:16:58,750
we have to find a way to undo the wish.

317
00:17:33,590 --> 00:17:34,930
That'll be rude.

318
00:17:45,160 --> 00:17:46,860
Forget it.

319
00:17:50,450 --> 00:17:52,050
Hello, good night.

320
00:17:52,570 --> 00:17:54,630
Do you want to ask about He Xiangyong?

321
00:17:56,850 --> 00:17:57,950
Our He Xiangyong

322
00:17:58,290 --> 00:18:00,310
has gone missing after something happened.

323
00:18:00,310 --> 00:18:01,780
I don't know where he is now.

324
00:18:01,780 --> 00:18:02,880
Did he call you?

325
00:18:03,460 --> 00:18:04,490
No.

326
00:18:04,890 --> 00:18:07,060
I came here just to figure it out.

327
00:18:07,080 --> 00:18:09,210
But he's gone. It's bothering me.

328
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:11,450
He didn't call you either?

329
00:18:11,890 --> 00:18:13,100
This little brat.

330
00:18:13,290 --> 00:18:14,010
Pick one.

331
00:18:22,800 --> 00:18:24,470
He's probably in trouble.

332
00:18:24,590 --> 00:18:25,390
What trouble?

333
00:18:26,270 --> 00:18:28,800
If you want to know,
find the answer yourself.

334
00:18:29,440 --> 00:18:30,800
Wait, you have to tell me

335
00:18:30,800 --> 00:18:32,420
what the card says

336
00:18:32,620 --> 00:18:34,280
and what kind of difficulties

337
00:18:34,290 --> 00:18:35,890
or what kind of person he met.

338
00:18:38,380 --> 00:18:40,180
I'm going to fulfill my mission.

339
00:18:41,700 --> 00:18:42,330
Miss.

340
00:18:45,900 --> 00:18:46,750
Miss.

341
00:18:47,050 --> 00:18:49,090
You haven't finished yet, you know?

342
00:19:08,050 --> 00:19:09,120
Li Wanzhe!

343
00:19:12,700 --> 00:19:14,300
I have something to tell you!

344
00:19:16,880 --> 00:19:17,950
Come here.

345
00:19:17,980 --> 00:19:19,780
I have something to tell you too.

346
00:19:19,850 --> 00:19:20,450
Sit.

347
00:19:34,420 --> 00:19:35,880
-Actually…
-Actually...

348
00:19:40,590 --> 00:19:41,330
-I...
-I...

349
00:19:46,550 --> 00:19:47,660
-You...
-You…

350
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:50,250
It's okay. You go first.

351
00:19:50,250 --> 00:19:51,270
You go first.

352
00:19:54,970 --> 00:19:56,230
Actually, I don't know

353
00:19:56,240 --> 00:19:58,040
why I suddenly confessed to you.

354
00:19:58,060 --> 00:19:59,390
-But I...
-Actually...

355
00:20:00,940 --> 00:20:03,140
there's a strange legend on our island.

356
00:20:04,010 --> 00:20:06,030
If there are shooting stars that day,

357
00:20:06,030 --> 00:20:07,190
then...

358
00:20:07,460 --> 00:20:09,230
then do something strange...

359
00:20:09,250 --> 00:20:10,180
Shooting stars?

360
00:20:10,360 --> 00:20:11,560
Yes, shooting stars.

361
00:20:11,870 --> 00:20:13,300
I think
it's only because of the shooting stars.

362
00:20:13,300 --> 00:20:14,120
You didn't like me at first,

363
00:20:14,120 --> 00:20:14,980
but now you do.

364
00:20:15,570 --> 00:20:16,670
Yes, that's it.

365
00:20:18,410 --> 00:20:19,710
I really like you.

366
00:20:20,240 --> 00:20:23,300
I really think
it's only because of the shooting stars.

367
00:20:23,300 --> 00:20:24,000
Trust me.

368
00:20:24,140 --> 00:20:25,150
Trust me.

369
00:20:25,470 --> 00:20:26,940
Trust what I trust.

370
00:20:26,960 --> 00:20:28,730
Trust the trust in what I trust.

371
00:20:32,470 --> 00:20:34,840
You go back and sleep.

372
00:20:34,870 --> 00:20:36,940
Everything will be fine
once you wake up tomorrow.

373
00:20:36,940 --> 00:20:38,060
It's just...

374
00:20:38,590 --> 00:20:40,210
just some weird power

375
00:20:40,230 --> 00:20:42,520
that made you suddenly
confess to me on impulse.

376
00:20:42,520 --> 00:20:43,950
Yes, that's it.

377
00:20:43,980 --> 00:20:44,930
Yes.

378
00:20:45,760 --> 00:20:47,690
I really like you.

379
00:20:54,560 --> 00:20:55,260
You like me?

380
00:20:56,670 --> 00:20:58,670
Okay, tell me what you like about me.

381
00:21:00,690 --> 00:21:02,090
I like your cute eyes.

382
00:21:02,120 --> 00:21:03,390
I like your high nose.

383
00:21:03,410 --> 00:21:04,610
I like your thick lips.

384
00:21:04,610 --> 00:21:05,730
I like your long legs.

385
00:21:05,730 --> 00:21:07,790
I like how you're so good to your family.

386
00:21:07,790 --> 00:21:09,760
I like that you're very considerate
to your friends.

387
00:21:09,760 --> 00:21:11,770
I like that you're cheerful to everyone.

388
00:21:11,770 --> 00:21:14,240
I like that whenever you make
shaved ice for me,

389
00:21:14,240 --> 00:21:17,340
you always add tons and tons
of plums for me.

390
00:21:17,540 --> 00:21:19,210
I like how you eat

391
00:21:19,230 --> 00:21:20,490
with such big, hearty bites.

392
00:21:20,490 --> 00:21:22,720
I want to eat a lot of delicious food
with you.

393
00:21:22,720 --> 00:21:23,550
Okay.

394
00:21:24,460 --> 00:21:25,730
Okay, I got it.

395
00:21:26,420 --> 00:21:28,350
Then... how are you gonna prove it?

396
00:21:29,380 --> 00:21:30,980
How do you want me to prove it?

397
00:21:34,320 --> 00:21:35,390
I see.

398
00:21:35,920 --> 00:21:37,580
Turtle-shaped cakes, right?

399
00:21:39,060 --> 00:21:41,260
I'll buy some for you tomorrow morning.

400
00:21:42,370 --> 00:21:43,500
Wait, wait.

401
00:21:44,760 --> 00:21:46,980
Turtle-shaped cakes. Okay?

402
00:21:52,530 --> 00:21:53,290
But...

403
00:21:54,230 --> 00:21:55,840
I prefer pork knuckle rice.

404
00:21:56,510 --> 00:21:59,710
Pork knuckle rice from Siping Street,
New Taipei, right?

405
00:21:59,900 --> 00:22:01,070
How do you know?

406
00:22:03,430 --> 00:22:04,840
Wait.

407
00:22:04,870 --> 00:22:06,030
There's more.

408
00:22:08,060 --> 00:22:08,760
I also want to eat

409
00:22:08,760 --> 00:22:10,290
charcoal-grilled sandwich
from Yancheng District, Kaohsiung,

410
00:22:10,290 --> 00:22:11,790
squid roll rice noodles
from Guohua Street, Tainan,

411
00:22:11,790 --> 00:22:13,160
white vinegar cold noodles
from Wenhua Road, Chiayi,

412
00:22:13,160 --> 00:22:14,020
Black Bamboo Chicken Feet Jelly,

413
00:22:14,020 --> 00:22:14,880
stinky tofu from Heping Road,

414
00:22:14,880 --> 00:22:16,030
jute leaf soup
from the Taichung Second Market,

415
00:22:16,030 --> 00:22:16,800
Popiah from Hsinchu City God Temple,

416
00:22:16,800 --> 00:22:19,730
and garlic pork thick soup
from Taishan Road, Yilan.

417
00:22:20,250 --> 00:22:21,190
What do you say?

418
00:22:21,220 --> 00:22:22,350
You can't do it, huh?

419
00:22:29,790 --> 00:22:30,760
Let me think.

420
00:22:39,180 --> 00:22:40,380
When you really do it,

421
00:22:40,420 --> 00:22:42,220
let's talk about why you like me.

422
00:22:50,310 --> 00:22:52,280
I don't think he can buy them.

423
00:22:53,040 --> 00:22:54,810
Yeah, he surely can't.

424
00:22:56,150 --> 00:22:57,650
Yeah, he can't.

425
00:22:57,680 --> 00:22:59,690
He can't.

426
00:23:01,320 --> 00:23:03,280
Jiao is so strange lately.

427
00:23:04,830 --> 00:23:06,120
She keeps coming to my clinic.

428
00:23:06,120 --> 00:23:08,720
She kept coming
even though she was doing fine.

429
00:23:09,850 --> 00:23:11,050
Turns out

430
00:23:11,270 --> 00:23:13,030
she came just to ask about you.

431
00:23:17,340 --> 00:23:18,140
What's wrong?

432
00:23:19,290 --> 00:23:20,420
Are you in a bad mood?

433
00:23:23,820 --> 00:23:25,520
My son

434
00:23:26,270 --> 00:23:27,630
must've gotten himself
into some kind of trouble,

435
00:23:27,630 --> 00:23:29,600
which is why he quit
his job and came home,

436
00:23:29,600 --> 00:23:31,000
and then, out of nowhere,

437
00:23:31,470 --> 00:23:32,720
some college friend of his showed up

438
00:23:32,720 --> 00:23:35,050
wanting to work for accommodation.

439
00:23:36,230 --> 00:23:37,760
I don't know what he's up to.

440
00:23:38,280 --> 00:23:40,150
I think something is off.

441
00:23:41,520 --> 00:23:43,320
Could something have happened?

442
00:23:43,850 --> 00:23:46,180
Why don't you go ask the publishing house?

443
00:23:49,560 --> 00:23:50,220
He's all grown up.

444
00:23:50,220 --> 00:23:52,220
Can't he solve everything himself?

445
00:23:54,540 --> 00:23:55,370
All right.

446
00:23:55,960 --> 00:23:57,400
Go on and act tough.

447
00:24:01,570 --> 00:24:03,370
I remember Xiangyong had a high fever

448
00:24:03,370 --> 00:24:04,430
when he was little.

449
00:24:05,240 --> 00:24:07,320
You carried him halfway
across the island just to find me.

450
00:24:07,320 --> 00:24:09,660
You even forgot to ride your motorcycle.

451
00:24:11,030 --> 00:24:12,690
Do you know what you said to me?

452
00:24:13,400 --> 00:24:14,200
What did I say?

453
00:24:14,840 --> 00:24:15,600
You said,

454
00:24:16,510 --> 00:24:17,450
"Worrying

455
00:24:17,480 --> 00:24:19,340
is a lifelong lesson for parents.

456
00:24:19,850 --> 00:24:21,910
No matter how old their children get,

457
00:24:22,690 --> 00:24:24,160
parents

458
00:24:24,560 --> 00:24:25,620
just can't let go."

459
00:24:26,560 --> 00:24:27,110
Right?

460
00:24:34,010 --> 00:24:36,300
I don't know why,
but everything you're saying

461
00:24:36,300 --> 00:24:38,240
just makes me sick.

462
00:24:39,430 --> 00:24:40,660
You'd better be.

463
00:24:43,420 --> 00:24:44,360
Forget it.

464
00:24:45,410 --> 00:24:46,950
He's all grown up now.

465
00:24:47,310 --> 00:24:50,370
This was supposed to be my time
to relax and take it easy.

466
00:24:50,920 --> 00:24:53,180
Your concern shows clearly on your face.

467
00:24:54,790 --> 00:24:57,550
Instead of drinking
and moping here with me,

468
00:24:57,840 --> 00:25:00,040
why don't you go get some clear answers?

469
00:25:00,130 --> 00:25:02,930
You have to know what's wrong
before you can fix it.

470
00:25:06,670 --> 00:25:08,200
You're the best at talking.

471
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:12,000
How long are you going
to keep folding that paper boat?

472
00:25:15,860 --> 00:25:16,990
I'll burn it for you.

473
00:25:17,150 --> 00:25:19,190
For me? Nonsense.

474
00:25:46,090 --> 00:25:47,740
Just close your eyes by the sea

475
00:25:47,740 --> 00:25:49,100
and count:

476
00:25:49,840 --> 00:25:51,960
1, 4, 2, 8, 5, 7.

477
00:25:52,280 --> 00:25:54,110
Wanzhe's shaved ice is super delicious.

478
00:25:54,110 --> 00:25:55,260
No bad picks at all.

479
00:25:55,620 --> 00:25:57,620
It's just that the tri-color taro balls
might take a little while,

480
00:25:57,620 --> 00:25:59,350
because they're freshly made.

481
00:26:10,400 --> 00:26:11,480
What's wrong?

482
00:26:15,400 --> 00:26:17,130
I just wanted to throw my towel.

483
00:26:51,700 --> 00:26:53,850
[Where Is My Home]

484
00:26:59,860 --> 00:27:00,860
Zhong Xiaoyou.

485
00:27:00,880 --> 00:27:02,280
I think something is wrong.

486
00:27:02,280 --> 00:27:03,320
What?

487
00:27:05,250 --> 00:27:07,240
When I brought breakfast to Xixi earlier,

488
00:27:07,240 --> 00:27:09,360
she stayed in her room
and wouldn't come out,

489
00:27:09,360 --> 00:27:10,720
and she was making
some really weird noises.

490
00:27:10,720 --> 00:27:11,920
Like this, like this.

491
00:27:14,170 --> 00:27:16,030
And she was smashing everything.

492
00:27:16,460 --> 00:27:17,990
Did someone come to see her?

493
00:27:18,990 --> 00:27:20,360
She should be fine.

494
00:27:21,750 --> 00:27:23,610
That's what a comics artist does.

495
00:27:23,800 --> 00:27:25,330
She's probably being urged to write.

496
00:27:25,330 --> 00:27:27,770
So she locked herself up
and let her second personality take over.

497
00:27:27,770 --> 00:27:28,610
But she can't lock

498
00:27:28,610 --> 00:27:30,070
herself in her room.

499
00:27:30,090 --> 00:27:31,310
What if something really happens?

500
00:27:31,310 --> 00:27:32,370
How can we help her?

501
00:27:32,650 --> 00:27:33,810
She'll be fine.

502
00:27:39,720 --> 00:27:40,450
Excuse me.

503
00:27:41,690 --> 00:27:43,160
I'll call Mr. He first.

504
00:27:43,530 --> 00:27:44,830
Chen Haowei.

505
00:27:46,970 --> 00:27:47,740
What's up?

506
00:27:49,600 --> 00:27:51,330
Why don't you go buy something?

507
00:27:51,820 --> 00:27:53,080
What do you want to buy?

508
00:27:53,400 --> 00:27:55,000
Bitter melons and black tea.

509
00:27:57,540 --> 00:27:58,500
Why me?

510
00:28:01,170 --> 00:28:01,900
Fine.

511
00:28:01,920 --> 00:28:03,160
Call Mr. He then.

512
00:28:03,370 --> 00:28:06,030
When he comes back,
the room should be torn down.

513
00:28:06,740 --> 00:28:09,200
You'll be responsible if anything happens.

514
00:28:10,880 --> 00:28:13,900
Should the green tea be sweetened or not?

515
00:28:14,150 --> 00:28:16,050
Black tea, sugar-free.

516
00:28:16,080 --> 00:28:17,660
Black tea, sugar-free.

517
00:28:22,020 --> 00:28:23,150
But Bitter melons
come in both white and green...

518
00:28:23,150 --> 00:28:24,060
Whatever.

519
00:28:24,920 --> 00:28:25,810
Go.

520
00:28:29,200 --> 00:28:30,170
Weird.

521
00:28:44,930 --> 00:28:46,530
What took him so long?

522
00:29:10,460 --> 00:29:12,150
Hello,
this is Where Is My Home Guesthouse.

523
00:29:12,150 --> 00:29:12,960
Xiaoyou.

524
00:29:13,210 --> 00:29:14,410
I'm going to the main island.

525
00:29:14,410 --> 00:29:16,560
We may have a group of fishing tourists
coming these days.

526
00:29:16,560 --> 00:29:17,820
Remember to reserve 5 rooms

527
00:29:17,820 --> 00:29:19,150
and avoid overbooking.

528
00:29:19,450 --> 00:29:20,520
Call me if anything happens.

529
00:29:20,520 --> 00:29:21,920
When are you coming back?

530
00:29:22,710 --> 00:29:23,470
Hello?

531
00:29:24,430 --> 00:29:25,270
Hello?

532
00:29:29,220 --> 00:29:30,820
You knew
there was a fishing tour group coming,

533
00:29:30,820 --> 00:29:33,280
yet left the guesthouse
to two part-timers.

534
00:29:46,960 --> 00:29:47,800
I'm back.

535
00:29:50,680 --> 00:29:51,850
Did you buy it right?

536
00:29:51,880 --> 00:29:52,960
Is it black tea?

537
00:29:53,060 --> 00:29:54,330
Yes.

538
00:29:54,870 --> 00:29:57,400
But I still bought
two kinds of bitter melons.

539
00:29:57,980 --> 00:29:58,690
It's okay.

540
00:29:58,690 --> 00:30:00,350
As long as it's a bitter melon.

541
00:30:15,280 --> 00:30:16,630
I made you a cup of tea

542
00:30:16,660 --> 00:30:17,990
and left it at your door.

543
00:30:42,740 --> 00:30:43,550
What's wrong?

544
00:30:43,930 --> 00:30:45,790
You also need to calm your nerves?

545
00:30:47,390 --> 00:30:48,120
No.

546
00:30:49,070 --> 00:30:50,690
I just want to see if it works.

547
00:30:55,930 --> 00:30:59,390
Haven't you heard
that sweetness always follows bitterness?

548
00:31:01,330 --> 00:31:02,540
The human brain

549
00:31:02,560 --> 00:31:05,260
produces 4 happiness-inducing chemicals:

550
00:31:05,290 --> 00:31:08,320
serotonin, dopamine,
endorphins, and oxytocin.

551
00:31:08,730 --> 00:31:11,410
The bitter taste of bitter melons
stimulates the release of endorphins,

552
00:31:11,410 --> 00:31:12,800
while the polyphenols in black tea

553
00:31:12,800 --> 00:31:14,400
have powerful antioxidant effects.

554
00:31:14,400 --> 00:31:16,460
That's why bitter melons
paired with black tea

555
00:31:16,460 --> 00:31:18,100
helps relieve anxiety.

556
00:31:19,590 --> 00:31:20,470
Really?

557
00:31:20,760 --> 00:31:21,570
Really.

558
00:31:21,940 --> 00:31:23,080
I read it in a book.

559
00:31:25,970 --> 00:31:27,840
Do you read this kind of book?

560
00:31:28,680 --> 00:31:29,780
Yes.

561
00:31:30,480 --> 00:31:31,910
I don't have many friends.

562
00:31:31,910 --> 00:31:33,640
I just read books when I'm free.

563
00:31:37,740 --> 00:31:39,910
You usually go on and on in circles.

564
00:31:41,100 --> 00:31:43,500
But you're pretty reliable when it counts.

565
00:31:47,270 --> 00:31:48,730
You didn't lie to me today.

566
00:31:51,970 --> 00:31:53,320
Did I lie to you a lot?

567
00:31:54,870 --> 00:31:56,340
If I truly lied to you,

568
00:31:57,130 --> 00:31:58,530
it was just one sentence.

569
00:32:00,710 --> 00:32:01,410
Which one?

570
00:32:06,400 --> 00:32:07,600
He said...

571
00:32:08,960 --> 00:32:11,560
you were the last person
he wanted to remember.

572
00:32:16,840 --> 00:32:18,300
The one on the first night,

573
00:32:18,300 --> 00:32:19,950
on the rooftop.

574
00:32:20,330 --> 00:32:21,700
At night?

575
00:32:22,370 --> 00:32:24,030
So which line was it, exactly?

576
00:32:24,900 --> 00:32:26,700
Forget it if you don't remember.

577
00:32:34,540 --> 00:32:35,400
How about this?

578
00:32:36,920 --> 00:32:38,380
Let's play a game.

579
00:32:39,090 --> 00:32:40,690
We ask each other a question,

580
00:32:40,950 --> 00:32:42,610
but we have to be honest, okay?

581
00:32:42,770 --> 00:32:43,770
What do you think?

582
00:32:47,030 --> 00:32:48,140
Go ahead.

583
00:32:58,460 --> 00:33:00,520
Did He Xiangyong leave because of me?

584
00:33:09,080 --> 00:33:09,950
No.

585
00:33:12,420 --> 00:33:13,190
Really?

586
00:33:14,650 --> 00:33:15,370
Really.

587
00:33:22,030 --> 00:33:22,890
Your turn.

588
00:33:40,950 --> 00:33:41,740
What?

589
00:33:47,150 --> 00:33:49,150
Have you dated He Xiangyong before?

590
00:33:52,060 --> 00:33:53,750
What exactly did you come to Xingpu Island

591
00:33:53,750 --> 00:33:55,320
to find him for?

592
00:34:07,830 --> 00:34:09,480
What is Chen Haowei doing?

593
00:34:07,890 --> 00:34:14,310
[Epilogue]

594
00:34:10,080 --> 00:34:12,010
Can't Chen Haowei quit dealing with
everything by himself all the time?

595
00:34:12,010 --> 00:34:13,780
Does he think he's Kobe Bryant?

596
00:34:14,400 --> 00:34:15,770
He might as well just play the whole game
by himself.

597
00:34:15,770 --> 00:34:17,230
About today, I'm sorry...

598
00:34:17,679 --> 00:34:19,380
Basketball is a team sport, okay?

599
00:34:19,380 --> 00:34:20,580
He kept taking shots,

600
00:34:20,600 --> 00:34:21,750
but he couldn't even make any.

601
00:34:21,750 --> 00:34:22,550
What the hell?

602
00:34:24,219 --> 00:34:26,480
I don't want to team up with him
next time.

603
00:34:49,800 --> 00:34:50,949
Why are you here?

604
00:34:51,340 --> 00:34:52,870
I'm fine.

605
00:34:53,040 --> 00:34:54,540
It's just a game.

606
00:34:58,370 --> 00:34:59,190
He Xiangyong.

607
00:34:59,390 --> 00:35:00,430
This way,

608
00:35:01,150 --> 00:35:02,400
no one will see how sad you are.

609
00:35:02,400 --> 00:35:03,470
Do you know why I came to you?

610
00:35:03,470 --> 00:35:04,890
I'm not sad.

611
00:35:05,160 --> 00:35:06,170
I'm fine.

612
00:35:06,920 --> 00:35:08,990
Can't you just laugh

613
00:35:09,090 --> 00:35:10,740
and cry whenever you want?

614
00:35:12,040 --> 00:35:13,270
You don't have to care

615
00:35:13,270 --> 00:35:14,170
what others think of Chen Haowei.

616
00:35:14,170 --> 00:35:15,770
Because as long as I find you,

617
00:35:16,810 --> 00:35:18,910
I think I can find myself.

618
00:35:52,430 --> 00:35:58,140
[Next Episode]

619
00:35:52,520 --> 00:35:53,290
He!

620
00:35:54,840 --> 00:35:56,240
Sorry to bother you guys.

621
00:35:56,780 --> 00:35:58,640
You are He Xiangyong, aren't you?

622
00:35:59,020 --> 00:36:00,720
You two aren't fighting,

623
00:36:00,720 --> 00:36:02,520
just being stubborn and moody.

624
00:36:02,520 --> 00:36:03,360
I said I wanted to see him

625
00:36:03,360 --> 00:36:04,660
because I want to beat him up.

626
00:36:04,660 --> 00:36:06,300
Surprise!

627
00:36:07,110 --> 00:36:07,810
Xiangyong.

628
00:36:07,940 --> 00:36:09,180
Your favorite watermelon candy.

